State Republican leaders will watch closely which Supreme Court choices President Obama submits as part of a coordinated strategy trying to make the court more conservative, a Georgia congressman said Wednesday.

"States have done a great job of protecting Georgia's interests," said U.S. Rep. Tom Graves, R-Ranger, spearheading the state's efforts.

Most have passed Right To Try laws that try to allow terminally ill patients to try experimental drugs that neither have been approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration nor been clinically tested.

But California legislators sued to try to get six Georgia pharmaceutical companies that manufacture experimental drugs in their state to put them there instead. The lawsuit was dropped last April, one day before a California judge was to rule against the group.
